  "dct_description_sm": [
    "New York City Historical Addresses, 1855-1915 is a point theme representing the location of building addresses in New York City between 1855 and 1915. This dataset is part of the NYC Space/Time Directory created by the New York Public Library and was created in part through data collected through the NYPL Building Inspector project. The source data for this dataset was downloaded in October of 2020 at this link: http://spacetime.nypl.org/#data which has further information about the creation of the data. Columbia libraries staff converted the \"flattened file\" GeoJSON file to the geopackage file format. All original filed are packaged in the direct download format."
